  <para>
    <classname>RemoveShortSide</classname> is a <xref
    linkend="RegisteredClass-Rationalizer"/> applied by the <xref
    linkend="RegisteredClass-Rationalize"/> &skel; <link
    linkend="RegisteredClass-SkeletonModifier">modifier</link>.  It
    removes the shortest segment of a quadrilateral &elem;, thus
    converting the &elem; into a triangle.  When used as part of a
    <xref linkend="RegisteredClass-SpecificRationalization"/>,
    <classname>RemoveShortSide</classname> is applied only to &elems;
    in which the ratio of the length of the second shortest side to
    the length of shortest side is greater than the given
    <varname>ratio</varname>.
  </para>
  <para>
    <xref linkend="Table:ration_short"/> summarizes the conditions
    under which <classname>RemoveShortSide</classname> applies, and
    the consequences of its application.
  </para>
